Privacy Policy for Blonk
Last updated: January 03, 2025

This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and disclose your personal data when you use the Blonk VR game and its related services, and your rights regarding your data. By using Blonk, you consent to the collection and use of your data as described in this policy.

Interpretation and Definitions
Interpretation
Words with capitalized initial letters have specific meanings under the following definitions, which apply to both singular and plural forms.

Definitions
For the purposes of this Privacy Policy:

Account: A unique account created for you to access and use the Blonk VR game and associated services.
Affiliate: An entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with a party, where "control" refers to ownership of more than 50% of shares or voting rights.
Company: "tcdblonk", the developer and operator of the Blonk game and its services.
Cookies: Small files placed on your device by the website or app to store browsing data, game progress, or preferences.
Country: The United Kingdom.
Device: Any hardware, including VR headsets, computers, mobile devices, or other electronics used to access Blonk and its services.
Personal Data: Any information that identifies or can be used to identify an individual.
Service: The Blonk VR game, its website, and related services.
Service Provider: Third-party companies or individuals who process personal data on behalf of the Company to provide or improve the Service.
Usage Data: Data collected automatically through the game or app, such as in-game actions, voice chat interactions, and controller movements.
Website: The online presence for Blonk, accessible from tcdblonk GitHub.
You: The individual using the Blonk game and services or the entity on whose behalf an individual is using them.
Collecting and Using Your Personal Data
Types of Data Collected
Personal Data
While using Blonk, we may ask for certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to:

First and Last Name (for user identification and support)
Usage Data (collected automatically during your use of the game and its services)
Usage Data
Usage Data is collected automatically and may include:

Device Information: Your VR headset model, controller usage, device ID, IP address, operating system, and browser type.
Game-Specific Data: Your in-game actions, locations, scores, and voice/chat logs during multiplayer sessions.
Performance Data: Statistics on your gameplay, including latency, errors, and connection details.
This data is collected to monitor and improve game performance, enhance player experience, and maintain security.

Tracking Technologies and Cookies
We use cookies and tracking technologies to enhance your experience with Blonk:

Cookies: Small files placed on your device to store preferences or progress.
Web Beacons: Used for in-game analytics and communication tracking.
Use of Your Personal Data
The Company may use your personal data for the following purposes:

To provide and maintain Blonk: Including features like voice chat, controller tracking, and gameplay data.
To improve your experience: Analyzing in-game behavior to improve mechanics, update features, and fix bugs.
To manage your account: Access to game progress, achievements, and multiplayer features.
To contact you: Via email or push notifications for game updates, security alerts, or promotional offers.
To analyze gameplay: Identifying trends, improving service quality, and preventing cheating or abuse.
Sharing of Your Personal Data
We may share your personal information in the following cases:

With Service Providers: To improve gameplay or resolve technical issues.
For business transactions: In case of a sale or transfer of assets, your data may be part of the transaction.
With affiliates or business partners: For collaboration or special promotions.
With other users: When you interact in public game areas or share content that other players may view.
With your consent: If you give us explicit permission to share your data.
Retention of Your Personal Data
We retain your personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined above. Usage data may be stored for a longer period to analyze game trends or for security purposes, unless a legal obligation requires retention for a longer period.

Transfer of Your Personal Data
Your data may be processed and stored in different locations, including outside your home country. By using Blonk, you consent to the transfer of your data to locations with varying privacy protections.

Deleting Your Personal Data
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal data. You can delete or update your information through your account settings or contact us directly to request deletion.

Disclosure of Your Personal Data
Business Transactions
In case of mergers, acquisitions, or asset sales, your data may be transferred. We will notify you before any transfer.

Law Enforcement
We may be required to disclose your data in response to legal requests or to protect the company’s rights.

Other Legal Requirements
We may disclose your data to:

Comply with legal obligations.
Protect our rights, safety, or the public’s safety.
Security of Your Personal Data
We employ commercially reasonable security measures to protect your personal data, but remember that no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.

Children's Privacy
Blonk does not knowingly collect data from children under 13. If we discover such data collection, we will take steps to delete it.

Links to Other Websites
Blonk may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices, and we encourage you to review their policies.

Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy. Any changes will be posted here with the updated date. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: ollie.pearson55@gmail.com
